<li>Grab a suitable pair of dumbbells for the weight rack using a neutral hand position, palms facing inwards. Sit on the bench with your back firmly against the backrest. Your head should be in a neutral position.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Rotate your hands so your palms are facing in front of you. Keep your elbows tucked into the sides of your body.</li>



<li>Exhale and bring the dumbbells up to chest height by flexing your elbows. Your forearms should be the only movers.</li>



<li>Pause briefly and squeeze your biceps as you come to the top position. Inhale and bring the dumbbells back to the starting position under control.</li>
</ol>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start" id="Tricep-Dumbbell-Exercises">Tricep Dumbbell Exercises</h2>



