<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start seated with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs.</li>



<li>Then, lean back to lay on the bench. As you lean back, lift your thighs slightly to help you move the dumbbells to the starting position.</li>



<li>At this point, you should be lying on the bench with your arms completely straight. The dumbbells should be directly above your chest.</li>



<li>Engage your core to bring a slight arch into your back. Retract (draw back) your shoulder blades and firmly press your upper back into the bench. Firmly plant both of your feet.</li>



<li>As you exhale, push your elbows out as you bring the inner plate down towards your chest.</li>



<li>After touching your chest with the weight, inhale as you straighten your arms to return to the starting position.</li>
